properties.areaDesc: King, WA; Snohomish, WA; Pierce, WA
properties.headline: Flood Warning issued February 7 at 3:37AM PST until February 7 at 11:30AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Seattle has extended the

* Flood Warning for Urban Areas and Small Streams in...
Southwestern Snohomish County in west central Washington...
Central King County in west central Washington...
Central Pierce County in west central Washington...

* Until 1130 AM PST Friday

* At 333 AM PST, Doppler radar and automated rain gauges indicated
another one to two inches of rain in the foothills and up to a
half inch of rain in the lowlands. The rain overnight combined
with additional rain will keep small streams running high as well
as keep the threat of urban flooding going through the morning
hours.

* Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Bellevue, Everett, Kent, Auburn, Marysville, Puyallup, North Bend,
Gold Bar, Carnation, Index, Renton, Redmond, Kirkland, Sammamish,
Bothell, Issaquah, Lake Stevens, Maple Valley, Covington and Bonney
Lake.
properties.instruction:
Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.

Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the
dangers of flooding.
